<subSubSection lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,773,1226,1281]" box="[151,773,1258,1281]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis box="[151,525,1258,1281]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<typeStatus box="[151,201,1258,1281]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Type</typeStatus>
species: 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[300,525,1258,1281]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Kritzlerius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="anomalus" status="sp. nov.">Kritzlerius anomalus</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[531,616,1258,1281]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, by monotypy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1330,2036]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis box="[151,285,1331,1356]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Etymology:</emphasis>
This genus is dedicated to Dr. Henry Kritzler, a passionate taxonomist of terebellids from the 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,272,1370,1396]" genus="Caribbean" pageId="70" pageNumber="4" rank="genus" status="new species, new genus">Caribbean</taxonomicName>
region.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1330,2036]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis box="[198,327,1411,1436]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
Tentacles of 
<specimenCount box="[482,598,1410,1436]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
, each 
<typeStatus box="[670,720,1410,1436]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">type</typeStatus>
in different group; short and thin tentacles on wide separated transverse membrane, dorsally attached to upper lip; and long and thick tentacles in two lateral groups on base of upper lip; two pairs of branchiae as long, thin, sessile filaments, from segment 2; eyespots present in two lateral groups; notopodial glandular tissue on segments 4–7; lateral lappets absent; notopodia from segment 3; notochaetae of 
<specimenCount box="[328,444,1570,1596]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
, short smooth, unilimbate, curved distally; and long, straight, unilimbate; neuropodia with uncini avicular in single rows from segment 10.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1330,2036]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
<emphasis box="[198,443,1651,1676]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Remarks: 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[318,443,1651,1676]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Kritzlerius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">Kritzlerius</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[451,560,1650,1676]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, was identified by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kritzler, H." box="[782,961,1650,1676]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="53 - 124" refId="ref62802" refString="Kritzler, H. (1984) Chapter 52. Family Terebellidae Grube 1950. In: Uebelacker, J. M. &amp; Johnson, P. G., (Ed.), Taxonomic Guide to the Polychaetes of the Northern Gulf of Mexico. Barry A. Vittor &amp; Associates Inc., Mobile, Alabama, 53 - 124." type="book chapter" year="1984">Kritzler (1984)</bibRefCitation>
, but he never formally named the taxon, nor a 
<typeStatus box="[220,270,1690,1716]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">type</typeStatus>
species designated, although he provided a detailed description. This genus belongs to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hessle" authorityYear="1917" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thelepodinae">Thelepodinae</taxonomicName>
because of the presence of sessile unbranched branchiae on the anterior thoracic segments, and the presence of uncini in single rows along the body.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="70.[151,1437,1330,2036]" lastBlockId="71.[151,1436,152,458]" lastPageId="71" lastPageNumber="72" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">
Precise information about the main characters of each genus in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hessle" authorityYear="1917" box="[959,1119,1810,1836]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thelepodinae">Thelepodinae</taxonomicName>
is presented by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P." pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="113 - 161" refId="ref62285" refString="Hutchings, P. (1997) The Terebellidae (Polychaeta) of Northern Australia with a key to all the described species of the region. In: Hanley, J. R., Caswell, G., Megirian, D. &amp; Larson, H. K. (Ed.), Proceedings of the Sixth International Marine Biological Workshop. The marine flora and fauna of Darwin Harbour, Northern Territory, Australia. Museum and Art Gallery of the Northern Territory and the Australian Marine Sciences Association, Darwin, Australia, 113 - 161." type="book chapter" year="1997">Hutchings (1997)</bibRefCitation>
. She includes four genera with long tentacular membrane, branchiae on segments 2 and 3, and notopodia beginning on segment 3, which are also characters presented by 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[972,1097,1891,1916]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Kritzlerius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" status="gen. nov">
<emphasis box="[972,1097,1891,1916]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Kritzlerius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1106,1210,1890,1916]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
.. Those genera are 
<taxonomicName authority="Hutchings, 1977" authorityName="Hutchings" authorityYear="1977" box="[151,513,1930,1956]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Decathelepus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[151,310,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Decathelepus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. A." box="[317,513,1930,1956]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="1 - 38" refId="ref62241" refString="Hutchings, P. A. (1977) Terebelliform Polychaeta of the families Ampharetidae, Terebellidae and Trichobranchidae from Australia, chiefly from Moreton Bay, Queensland. Records of the Australian Museum, 31 (1), 1 - 38." type="journal article" year="1977">Hutchings, 1977</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hutchings and Glasby, 1986" authorityName="Hutchings and Glasby" authorityYear="1986" box="[526,1047,1930,1956]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Glossothelepus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[526,705,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Glossothelepus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J." box="[713,1047,1930,1956]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="105 - 117" refId="ref62388" refString="Hutchings, P. A. &amp; Glasby, C. J. (1986) A revision of the genus Euthelepus (Terebellidae: Thelepinae). Records of the Australian Museum, 38, 105 - 117." type="journal article" year="1986">Hutchings and Glasby, 1986</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authority="Hutchings, 1974" authorityName="Hutchings" authorityYear="1974" box="[1060,1431,1930,1956]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Rhinothelepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1060,1228,1931,1956]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Rhinothelepus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hutchings, P. A." box="[1235,1431,1930,1956]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="175 - 195" refId="ref62207" refString="Hutchings, P. A. (1974) Polychaeta of Wallis Lake, New South Wales. Proceedings of the Linnean Society of New South Wales, 98, 175 - 195." type="journal article" year="1974">Hutchings, 1974</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Day, 1955" authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1955" box="[203,487,1970,1996]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Telothelepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[203,350,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Telothelepus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Day, J. H." box="[360,487,1970,1996]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" pagination="407 - 452" refId="ref60872" refString="Day, J. H. (1955) The Polychaeta of South Africa. Sedentary species from Cape Shores and estuaries. Journal of the Linnean Society of London, 42 (2870), 407 - 452." type="journal article" year="1955">Day, 1955</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Nevertheless, all these genera differ from 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[1009,1134,1971,1996]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Kritzlerius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1009,1134,1971,1996]" italics="true" pageId="70" pageNumber="71">Kritzlerius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1144,1256,1970,1996]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, in having one group of tentacles of one length and thickness, 15 thoracic segments with notochaetae, and 
<specimenCount box="[1294,1399,2010,2036]" pageId="70" pageNumber="71" type="generic" typeStatus="type">one type</specimenCount>
of notochaetae thin, unilimbate, smooth-tipped. Additionally, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hutchings" authorityYear="1977" box="[841,1000,152,177]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Decathelepus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[841,1000,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Decathelepus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has uncini from segment 10, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hutchings and Glasby" authorityYear="1986" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Glossothelepus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Glossothelepus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has uncini from segment 9, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hutchings" authorityYear="1974" box="[593,760,192,217]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Rhinothelepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[593,760,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Rhinothelepus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has uncini from segment 8, and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Day" authorityYear="1955" box="[1158,1305,192,217]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Telothelepus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1158,1305,192,217]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Telothelepus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has uncini from segment 18. In contrast, 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[501,626,232,257]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Kritzlerius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus" status="gen. nov.">
<emphasis box="[501,626,232,257]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Kritzlerius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[634,743,232,258]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" rank="genus">gen. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, has more than 20 thoracic segments with notochaetae, two isolated groups of tentacles with different length and thickness, 
<specimenCount box="[914,1029,272,298]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of notochaetae, and uncini beginning on segment 10.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="71.[151,1436,152,458]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">
Thus, after the revision of the material, I conclude that this material belongs to a new genus because of the characters stated above, and they are not seen in other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hessle" authorityYear="1917" box="[787,950,392,418]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Thelepodinae">Thelepodinae</taxonomicName>
. The genus is established, diagnosed, and 
<taxonomicName authority="Londoño-Mesa, 2009" authorityName="Londoño-Mesa" authorityYear="2009" box="[151,397,432,457]" class="Polychaeta" family="Terebellidae" genus="Kritzlerius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Terebellida" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="anomalus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,397,432,457]" italics="true" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">Kritzlerius anomalus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[405,498,432,458]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, is described as its 
<typeStatus box="[723,774,432,458]" pageId="71" pageNumber="72">type</typeStatus>
species.
</paragraph>
